articles.description: Miles Reynolds scored 25 points and hit the game-winning jump shot with 3.5 seconds remaining to lift Pacific over Portland 60-58 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Reynolds hits late jumper; Pacific beats Portland 60-58

articles.description: The No. 12 Bulldogs get a hot start and don't look back, beating the No. 11 Gaels 78-65 on the road, snapping the longest active win streak in the nation.
articles.headline: Gonzaga ends Saint Mary's 19-game win streak

images.caption: The No. 12 Bulldogs get a hot start and don't look back, beating the No. 11 Gaels 78-65 on the road, snapping the longest active win streak in the nation.

articles.description: Zach Braxton scored a career-high 25 points and tied a career high with 13 rebounds and Weber State beat Northern Colorado 71-66 in overtime on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Braxton, Harding lift Weber St. past N. Colorado 71-66 in OT

articles.description: Donte Clark scored 26 points with nine rebounds and five assists and Texas Southern beat Jackson State 86-75 on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Clark with 26 leads Texas Southern past Jackson State 86-75

articles.description: David Collette scored 18 points on 9-of-10 shooting in a dominant performance around the paint and led Utah to a 77-43 win over California on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Utah dominates California for 77-43 win

articles.description: Rui Hachimura scored 23 points and No. 12 Gonzaga kept the ball out of Jock Landale's hands to end the nation's longest active winning streak at 19 games with a 78-65 victory over No. 11 Saint Mary's on Saturday night.
articles.headline: Gonzaga snaps Saint Mary's 19-game win streak, 78-65
